Docker container steps

install docker - *created and used docker script*

check docker is running - sudo systemctl status docker

check docker is working and running correctly - docker run hello-world

To search for the image you want to use, in this case ubuntu. - docker search ubuntu

find desired image and then pulll it down - docker pull ubuntu

to view list of timages that have been pulled and installed - docker images

To then run the conatiner with the image - docker run -it ubuntu

To list containers - sudo docker container ps -l

to remove a container - sudo docker rm *container name or ID*

To remove all of the contaienrs that you have created - sudo docker conatiner prune

To log into docker - docker login -u **your docker username**

To push online - docker push **Docker username** and then select want your pushing


